---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import ServiceCta from "../../components/ServiceCta.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import bannerImage from "../../assets/photos/crawler-underwater.jpg";
import supervisionImage from "../../assets/photos/crawler-supervision.jpg";
import filtrationImage from "../../assets/photos/filtration-detail.jpg";
import dischargeImage from "../../assets/photos/filtration-discharge.jpg";
import progressImage from "../../assets/photos/cleaning-progress-hud.jpg";
import costGraph from "../../assets/photos/fouling-cost-graph.jpg";
import crawlerToolImage from "../../assets/photos/iwc-crawler.jpg";
import puBladeImage from "../../assets/photos/iwc-pu-blade.jpg";
import nylonBladeImage from "../../assets/photos/iwc-nylon-blade.jpg";
import obdToolImage from "../../assets/photos/iwc-obd-tool.jpg";
import taperNozzleImage from "../../assets/photos/iwc-taper-nozzle.jpg";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Cleaning with Capture | MarineStream™"
  description="In-water hull and niche-area cleaning with capture, 10μ filtration and UV treatment aligned to IMO and Australian standards."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Services"
    title="Cleaning with capture"
    lead="In-water cleaning with capture, aligned to IMO and Australian biosecurity requirements."
    parent={{ href: "/services", label: "Services" }}
    image={bannerImage}
    imageAlt="Hull cleaning unit working on a ship's underwater hull"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Overview</span>
      <h2>Clean the hull, keep the fouling</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <p>
        Open in-water cleaning spreads exactly the organisms a clean is meant to control, which is
        why it is restricted in most Australian ports. Cleaning with capture removes fouling and
        contains it: dislodged material is drawn to the surface, filtered to 10μ, treated with UV,
        and disposed of properly, with nothing returned to the water untreated.
      </p>
      <ul class="checklist checklist--cols">
        <li>Capture and filtration to 10μ, with UV treatment</li>
        <li>Single 20′ container, deployable from wharf or support vessel</li>
        <li>Works with divers, hand tools, and ROV systems</li>
        <li>Niche areas: sea chests, shafts, rudders, thrusters</li>
        <li>Every clean recorded against the survey that triggered it</li>
        <li>Aligned to IMO guidance and Australian biosecurity requirements</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow">Why it pays</span>
          <h2>Fouling is a fuel bill and an emissions bill</h2>
          <hr class="accent-rule" />
          <p>
            Even light fouling raises hull resistance, and the cost compounds with speed: more fuel
            burned, more CO2 emitted, and a vessel that no longer meets its performance claims.
            Cleaning restores the hull; capture makes the clean itself compliant.
          </p>
          <p>
            Put your own numbers in with the
            <a href="/interactive-tools/hullCalc.html">Fouling Cost Calculator</a>, built on the
            same relationship shown here.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="figure reveal" style="margin: 0;">
          <Image
            src={costGraph}
            alt="Chart of operating cost and additional CO2 emissions against speed for clean and fouled hulls"
            widths={[480, 960]}
            sizes="(min-width: 800px) 32rem, 100vw"
            loading="lazy"
            style="background: #fff;"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Operating cost and additional CO2 for a fouled hull (FR1) against a clean hull (FR0).
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">How a clean runs</span>
      <h2>Survey to sign-off</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Survey</strong>
          <p>Fouling is rated first, so the clean is justified and the baseline is recorded.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Clean</strong>
          <p>Crawler, diver, or hand tools work the hull and niches with capture running.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Capture</strong>
          <p>Dislodged material is filtered to 10μ and UV treated. No open discharge.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Record</strong>
          <p>Before and after evidence lands in the platform with the waste stream documented.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">In-water cleaning methods</span>
      <h2>One backbone, three ways to clean</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <p style="max-width: var(--narrow);">
        A robotic crawler for hull plating, diver-operated hand tools for niche areas, and
        dedicated capture tools for penetrations. Change the tool, not the biosecurity outcome —
        every head returns its effluent through the same uplift line into the four-stage filtration
        system.
      </p>

      <div class="spec-cards">
        <article class="spec-card reveal">
          <div class="spec-card__media">
            <Image
              src={crawlerToolImage}
              alt="Magnetic hull crawler with cavitation cleaning head and dual capture ports"
              widths={[480, 900]}
              sizes="(min-width: 900px) 28rem, 100vw"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="spec-card__body">
            <span class="spec-card__eyebrow">Robotic hull-plating cleaning</span>
            <h3>Magnetic crawler · cavitation</h3>
            <dl class="spec-list">
              <div><dt>Adhesion</dt><dd>Permanent magnetic tracks</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Cleaning head</dt><dd>Cavitation — fresh water, ≈200 bar</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Capture</dt><dd>Custom shroud, dual exhaust ports</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Recovery</dt><dd>≈1,200 L/min to filtration</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Path width</dt><dd>450 mm per pass</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Depth / control</dt><dd>60 m · tethered console, cameras</dd></div>
            </dl>
            <p>Proven on Royal Australian Navy vessels — Australia's first robotic in-water hull clean with full biofouling capture.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="spec-card reveal">
          <div class="spec-card__media spec-card__media--contain">
            <Image
              src={puBladeImage}
              alt="Polyurethane-bladed diver hand tool for soft fouling"
              widths={[320, 480]}
              sizes="14rem"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <Image
              src={nylonBladeImage}
              alt="Nylon-bladed diver hand tool for hard fouling"
              widths={[320, 480]}
              sizes="14rem"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="spec-card__body">
            <span class="spec-card__eyebrow">Niche-area hand tools</span>
            <h3>Diver-operated · suction-through-head</h3>
            <dl class="spec-list">
              <div><dt>PU blade</dt><dd>Soft fouling, delicate coatings</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Nylon blade</dt><dd>Hard macrofouling</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Blades</dt><dd>Interchangeable push / pull, swapped underwater</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Capture</dt><dd>Suction at the blade as debris lifts</dd></div>
            </dl>
            <p>Interchangeable blades let the diver match soft or hard fouling without leaving the water.</p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="spec-card reveal">
          <div class="spec-card__media spec-card__media--contain">
            <Image
              src={obdToolImage}
              alt="Valve-isolated rotary capture cup for overboard discharges"
              widths={[320, 480]}
              sizes="14rem"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <Image
              src={taperNozzleImage}
              alt="Tapered suction nozzle for reaching recesses and crevices"
              widths={[320, 480]}
              sizes="14rem"
              loading="lazy"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="spec-card__body">
            <span class="spec-card__eyebrow">Penetration &amp; OBD cleaning</span>
            <h3>Capture cups · taper nozzles</h3>
            <dl class="spec-list">
              <div><dt>OBD tool</dt><dd>Valve-isolated rotary capture cup</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Targets</dt><dd>Overboard discharges, intakes, gratings</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Taper nozzle</dt><dd>Reaches recesses and crevices</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Connection</dt><dd>Camlock straight to the uplift line</dd></div>
            </dl>
            <p>Dedicated capture tooling for penetrations that a crawler or blade cannot seal against.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <figure class="figure reveal" style="margin: 0;">
          <Image
            src={progressImage}
            alt="Live cleaning telemetry showing the boundary between fouled and cleaned hull"
            widths={[480, 900]}
            sizes="(min-width: 800px) 32rem, 100vw"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Mid-clean telemetry: the boundary between fouled and cleaned plating, recorded live.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow">Proof, not promises</span>
          <h2>The clean documents itself</h2>
          <hr class="accent-rule" />
          <p>
            Cleaning systems record as they work. Progress, coverage, and the fouled-to-clean
            boundary are captured frame by frame, so the report is generated from evidence rather
            than written after the fact.
          </p>
          <p>
            Capture matters where open cleaning is restricted. Every clean lands in the same
            digital record as the inspection that triggered it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">The capture system</span>
      <h2>Captured, filtered, disinfected — no open discharge</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <p>
        Whichever tool does the cleaning, the effluent is lifted to a single 20′ container and
        passes through four filtration stages before it returns to the harbour. Every drop goes
        through every stage — there is no bypass — and the solids leave the site as documented
        waste.
      </p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Bow screen</strong>
          <p>Coarse solids separated to a catch bag; filtrate drains to the bund.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>25 μm screen</strong>
          <p>Self-cleaning micro-screen swept continuously by twin spraybars.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bag filter</strong>
          <p>Eight parallel housings polish the stream down to 5 μm.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>UV disinfection</strong>
          <p>Quartz-sleeved UV array inactivates organisms before discharge.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="photo-pair" style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
        <Image
          src={filtrationImage}
          alt="Open containerised filtration plant with stainless vessel and pumps on a wharf"
          widths={[480, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 560px) 21rem, 100vw"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <Image
          src={dischargeImage}
          alt="Filtration barge returning treated water to the harbour beside a vessel"
          widths={[480, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 560px) 21rem, 100vw"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <p>
        The plant runs from the wharf or a support vessel alongside, capturing to ≤10 μm with UV
        treatment and holding dissolved copper to ≤ 3.8 ppb in discharge. The same unit supports
        <a href="/services/inspection">inspection</a> and diver operations, and the full
        specification is on the <a href="/services/hardware">hardware</a> page for partners running
        their own cleans.
      </p>
      <div class="figure reveal">
        <Image
          src={supervisionImage}
          alt="Operator supervising a hull crawler working at a ship's waterline"
          widths={[480, 900]}
          sizes="(min-width: 800px) 42rem, 100vw"
          loading="lazy"
          style="width: 100%; border-radius: var(--radius);"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ServiceCta
    title="Scope a compliant clean"
    lead="Tell us the vessel, the fouling state if you know it, and the port. We will confirm the approach and what the record needs to show."
    primaryHref="/contact"
    primaryLabel="Enquire about cleaning"
    secondaryHref="/services/inspection"
    secondaryLabel="Start with a survey"
  />
</SiteLayout>
